title: 0  fiat amount despite having tokens in Wallet
body: ### Description *Type*: Bug *Summary*: Wallet showed $0.00 due to 504 cryptocompare api error. Maybe we can retry the call? Or at least call the API whenever Wallet tab is opened. ### Reproduction - ### Additional Information * Status version: 0.9.24 * Operating System: Android, iOS

The immediate issue here is that there was an error when app tried to fetch currency conversion rates for tokens and that error was never communicated to the user. Instead, users only knew that something is wrong because the USD amount was zero.

E.g. in this case we might display an error message saying e.g. `Error while getting currency conversion rates. Displayed amounts may not be accurate.` or something like that.

It turns out that we actually do capture this error (as well as error during balance update), but we never actually show it anywhere. We'll need some UI design for error messages in Wallet or generally in the app (couldn't find in zeplin)

cc @denis-sharypin @obi2020

@goranjovic yet another user has experienced this issue. Would be great to include some fix in the next week release. I think your error message is a good starting point. @obi2020 could you review it? Maybe instead of "Error" we should use a different word like "Oops, .." to make it more user friendly.

Hey all,

Currently, we have 3 UIs to show errors in the app. Let's pick one that fits our need here and don't create a new one.

![errors](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6559881/43713814-d141f6dc-9972-11e8-931e-aef01945ae17.jpg)

What do you think could work here better?
It will be shown every time the Wallet tab is opened. So, I'm wondering if we should show the alert every time. Maybe it's better to display the snackbar? @denis-sharypin wdyt?

Considering the limited spaces, I want to focus on what's most important for the user to know. Could you weigh in on which of the following is crucial and which can be cut? These are not final copy, just key points of info related to the error

- There was a problem retrieving currency conversion rates 
- The error may have cause total value to display incorrectly 
- Please refresh your screen for an update 

The last of these is a guess / placeholder for what the user should do next. Here are a few tries:

> "Currency conversion error. Refresh to update"
> 
> "Conversion error causing incorrect totals. Please refresh"
> 
> "Currency rates not current. Refresh to update total"

Great! I personally like `Currency conversion error. Try to refresh to update later`
I would add something like `later` to the end of the phrase since this error on the side of another app and we don't know how soon it would be fixed
@goranjovic  do we support 2 (or more )lines of text in the snackbar? Could you kindly check it out?

@denis-sharypin Will do, thanks. That's my favorite too.

Btw, snackbar - cool name
@denis-sharypin Only one line
@goranjovic. Can we make the height of the bar expandable to required text amount?
@denis-sharypin No, it uses absolute positioning.

Desired behaivor 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6559881/43837292-f02521fc-9b0f-11e8-91e5-2cbd6a8f6660.png)

@denis-sharypin @obi2020 

Working version screenshot attached.
We're not sure yet why users who get this error can't access this api, but from the reports we've received so far the problem persists for quite a while, so we need to communicate that somehow.

![screenshot-2018-08-08_18 41 48 261](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/711764/43851363-c38cfb8a-9b3a-11e8-8c76-45cf4070dc1f.png)
looks good to me!

My only qualm is with "later" - it's too vague. I know that we don't know when the issue will resolve, but can we give some guide:

"Currency conversion error. Wait # minutes, then refresh to update."

@obi2020 The problem is that we don't really have any estimate when it would work again. Or what's the reason why it doesn't work. E.g. if cryptocompare is say blocked in some countries, then it won't work at all there, no matter how long you wait. 

And to be fair, in that case "later" is just as misleading :/
@goranjovic  so we can't track either it's a cryptocompare is down or blocked?
@denis-sharypin we can get some idea from the logs, if we get them, but generally no

@naghdy had this issue recently. I believe it was still on the old build so he did not see a snackbar with wallet errors. 
Anyway, here is his logcat. There are no entries about cryptocompare api requests. @goranjovic maybe there is a different reason for this issue?
